#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.76"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.76:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.76:0.2"
msgid "8. Gilānavagga"
msgstr "8. Sick"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 76. Rādhaaniccasutta → aniccasuttaṃ (bj) | rādha 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.76:0.3"
msgid "76. Rādhaaniccasutta"
msgstr "76. With Rādha on Impermanence"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.49"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.76:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā rādho … pe …"
msgstr "The Venerable Rādha went up to the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.2"
msgid "ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.3"
msgid ""
"“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato "
"dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’"
"ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ kho, rādha, aniccaṃ tatra te chando pahātabbo."
msgstr "“Rādha, you should give up desire for what is impermanent."

# Reading follows PTS, BB, see following suttas.
msgctxt "sn35.76:1.5"
msgid "Kiñca, rādha, aniccaṃ tatra te chando pahātabbo?"
msgstr "And what is impermanent?"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.6"
msgid "Cakkhu aniccaṃ, rūpā aniccā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr "The eye, sights, eye consciousness,"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.7"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso …"
msgstr "and eye contact are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.8"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccaṃ. Tatra te chando pahātabbo … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye "
"contact is also impermanent. You should give up desire for it."

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.9"
msgid "jivhā …"
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.10"
msgid "kāyo …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.11"
msgid "mano anicco. Tatra te chando pahātabbo."
msgstr "The mind,"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.12"
msgid "Dhammā …"
msgstr "thoughts,"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.13"
msgid "manoviññāṇaṃ …"
msgstr "mind consciousness,"

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.14"
msgid "manosamphasso …"
msgstr "and mind contact are impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.15"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccaṃ. Tatra te chando pahātabbo."
msgstr ""
"And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by "
"mind contact is also impermanent. You should give up desire for it."

msgctxt "sn35.76:1.16"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, rādha, aniccaṃ tatra te chando pahātabbo”ti."
msgstr "You should give up desire for what is impermanent.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.76:1.17"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
